{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01AfxYpE4RBeXH8VZdwSLs5P","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete picture of all KubeletConfig patterns. Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## KubeletConfig in Machine Config Operator: Findings\n\n### 1. Creating a KubeletConfig Targeting Worker Nodes\n\nThere are two supported patterns for `machineConfigPoolSelector`:\n\n**Pattern A — Built-in pool label (OCP 4.6+, recommended):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n**Pattern B — Custom label (pre-4.6 or custom pools):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      custom-kubelet: small-pods\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\nWith Pattern B, you must manually label the MachineConfigPool:\n```\noc edit machineconfigpool worker\n# add \"custom-kubelet: small-pods\" under metadata.labels\n```\n\nKey file: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md` (lines 72–127)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Setting maxPods and podPidsLimit\n\n**maxPods** is a first-class kubelet config field. Examples from the codebase:\n\n- Simple YAML example (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml`):\n  ```yaml\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n  ```\n\n- From the test data template (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-maxpods-kubelet-config.yaml`), setting `maxPods: 500`.\n\n- The worker default kubelet config (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/worker/01-worker-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`, line 20) has `maxPods: 250` and `podPidsLimit: 4096` as defaults.\n\n**podPidsLimit** is set via `kubeletConfig` the same way. The default is `4096` across all node roles (worker, master, arbiter). To override it via a KubeletConfig CR:\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-pids-limit\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 500\n    podPidsLimit: 8192\n```\n\nFiles with default values:\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/worker/01-worker-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/master/01-master-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/arbiter/01-arbiter-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Complete YAML Examples\n\n**Canonical minimal example** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml`):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      custom-kubelet: small-pods\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n**With logLevel** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md`, lines 74–85):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  logLevel: 5\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n**With autoSizingReserved** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md`, lines 169–179):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: dynamic-node\nspec:\n  autoSizingReserved: true\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n```\n\n**With custom TLS profile** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-tls-profile-kubelet-config.yaml`):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: \"${NAME}\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  tlsSecurityProfile:\n    type: Custom\n    custom:\n      ciphers:\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      minTLSVersion: VersionTLS11\n```\n\n**Generic template (pass any kubeletConfig as JSON)** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-kubelet-config.yaml`): uses `${{KUBELETCONFIG}}` as a template parameter.\n\n---\n\n### 4. machineConfigPoolSelector Patterns\n\nThe selector targets a MachineConfigPool by matching its labels. Three patterns are used in this repo:\n\n| Target | Label key | Label value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Worker pool (OCP 4.6+) | `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker` | `\"\"` |\n| Master pool (OCP 4.6+) | `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/master` | `\"\"` |\n| Custom/infra pool | `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/<poolname>` | `\"\"` |\n| Custom label (any version) | any user-defined key (e.g. `custom-kubelet`) | any user-defined value (e.g. `small-pods`) |\n\nThe canonical label for the worker MachineConfigPool is confirmed in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` and in many controller tests.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Go Struct Reference\n\nThe `KubeletConfigSpec` struct (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go`, lines 735–771):\n\n```go\ntype KubeletConfigSpec struct {\n    AutoSizingReserved        *bool                        `json:\"autoSizingReserved,omitempty\"`\n    LogLevel                  *int32                       `json:\"logLevel,omitempty\"`\n    MachineConfigPoolSelector *metav1.LabelSelector        `json:\"machineConfigPoolSelector,omitempty\"`\n    KubeletConfig             *runtime.RawExtension        `json:\"kubeletConfig,omitempty\"`\n    TLSSecurityProfile        *configv1.TLSSecurityProfile `json:\"tlsSecurityProfile,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n`kubeletConfig` is a `RawExtension` — its contents must be a serialized `kubelet.config.k8s.io/v1beta1` `KubeletConfiguration`. Fields like `maxPods` and `podPidsLimit` are upstream Kubernetes fields from that type. In tests they are constructed with `EncodeKubeletConfig(&kubeletconfigv1beta1.KubeletConfiguration{MaxPods: 100}, ...)` (see `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/kubelet-config/kubelet_config_controller_test.go`, lines 192–210).\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md` | Full design doc with examples, workflow, and `oc` commands |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml` | Minimal canonical YAML example |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-maxpods-kubelet-config.yaml` | maxPods test template |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-kubelet-config.yaml` | Generic parameterized template |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-tls-profile-kubelet-config.yaml` | TLS profile example |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/e2e-2of2/kubeletcfg_test.go` | E2E tests showing maxPods and multi-config workflows |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/kubelet-config/kubelet_config_controller_test.go` | Unit tests with `newKubeletConfig` helper and selector patterns |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go` (lines 722–831) | Full Go type definitions for `KubeletConfig`, `KubeletConfigSpec`, `KubeletConfigStatus` |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/worker/01-worker-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml` | Default kubelet.conf showing `maxPods: 250`, `podPidsLimit: 4096` |"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2fd8390-c847-413c-9495-3acc22b6bd40","uuid":"b10ea249-442b-4dc4-b182-88a78e847492","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:06:59.823Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search for KubeletConfig examples, documentation, and usage patterns in this Machine Config Operator repository. I need to understand:\n1. How to create a KubeletConfig resource targeting worker nodes\n2. How to set maxPods and podPidsLimit settings\n3. Any relevant YAML examples or test files showing complete KubeletConfig specs\n4. What machineConfigPoolSelector looks like\n\nSearch in: docs/, examples/, test/, pkg/, vendor/ for KubeletConfig YAML examples and Go structs. Search breadth: medium.","agentId":"a2cc8654419f1bf46","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete picture of all KubeletConfig patterns. Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## KubeletConfig in Machine Config Operator: Findings\n\n### 1. Creating a KubeletConfig Targeting Worker Nodes\n\nThere are two supported patterns for `machineConfigPoolSelector`:\n\n**Pattern A — Built-in pool label (OCP 4.6+, recommended):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n**Pattern B — Custom label (pre-4.6 or custom pools):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      custom-kubelet: small-pods\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\nWith Pattern B, you must manually label the MachineConfigPool:\n```\noc edit machineconfigpool worker\n# add \"custom-kubelet: small-pods\" under metadata.labels\n```\n\nKey file: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md` (lines 72–127)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Setting maxPods and podPidsLimit\n\n**maxPods** is a first-class kubelet config field. Examples from the codebase:\n\n- Simple YAML example (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml`):\n  ```yaml\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n  ```\n\n- From the test data template (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-maxpods-kubelet-config.yaml`), setting `maxPods: 500`.\n\n- The worker default kubelet config (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/worker/01-worker-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`, line 20) has `maxPods: 250` and `podPidsLimit: 4096` as defaults.\n\n**podPidsLimit** is set via `kubeletConfig` the same way. The default is `4096` across all node roles (worker, master, arbiter). To override it via a KubeletConfig CR:\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-pids-limit\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 500\n    podPidsLimit: 8192\n```\n\nFiles with default values:\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/worker/01-worker-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/master/01-master-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/arbiter/01-arbiter-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Complete YAML Examples\n\n**Canonical minimal example** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml`):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      custom-kubelet: small-pods\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n**With logLevel** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md`, lines 74–85):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: set-max-pods\nspec:\n  logLevel: 5\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n**With autoSizingReserved** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md`, lines 169–179):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: dynamic-node\nspec:\n  autoSizingReserved: true\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n```\n\n**With custom TLS profile** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-tls-profile-kubelet-config.yaml`):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: \"${NAME}\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  tlsSecurityProfile:\n    type: Custom\n    custom:\n      ciphers:\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      minTLSVersion: VersionTLS11\n```\n\n**Generic template (pass any kubeletConfig as JSON)** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-kubelet-config.yaml`): uses `${{KUBELETCONFIG}}` as a template parameter.\n\n---\n\n### 4. machineConfigPoolSelector Patterns\n\nThe selector targets a MachineConfigPool by matching its labels. Three patterns are used in this repo:\n\n| Target | Label key | Label value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Worker pool (OCP 4.6+) | `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker` | `\"\"` |\n| Master pool (OCP 4.6+) | `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/master` | `\"\"` |\n| Custom/infra pool | `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/<poolname>` | `\"\"` |\n| Custom label (any version) | any user-defined key (e.g. `custom-kubelet`) | any user-defined value (e.g. `small-pods`) |\n\nThe canonical label for the worker MachineConfigPool is confirmed in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` and in many controller tests.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Go Struct Reference\n\nThe `KubeletConfigSpec` struct (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go`, lines 735–771):\n\n```go\ntype KubeletConfigSpec struct {\n    AutoSizingReserved        *bool                        `json:\"autoSizingReserved,omitempty\"`\n    LogLevel                  *int32                       `json:\"logLevel,omitempty\"`\n    MachineConfigPoolSelector *metav1.LabelSelector        `json:\"machineConfigPoolSelector,omitempty\"`\n    KubeletConfig             *runtime.RawExtension        `json:\"kubeletConfig,omitempty\"`\n    TLSSecurityProfile        *configv1.TLSSecurityProfile `json:\"tlsSecurityProfile,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n`kubeletConfig` is a `RawExtension` — its contents must be a serialized `kubelet.config.k8s.io/v1beta1` `KubeletConfiguration`. Fields like `maxPods` and `podPidsLimit` are upstream Kubernetes fields from that type. In tests they are constructed with `EncodeKubeletConfig(&kubeletconfigv1beta1.KubeletConfiguration{MaxPods: 100}, ...)` (see `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/kubelet-config/kubelet_config_controller_test.go`, lines 192–210).\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md` | Full design doc with examples, workflow, and `oc` commands |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml` | Minimal canonical YAML example |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-maxpods-kubelet-config.yaml` | maxPods test template |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-kubelet-config.yaml` | Generic parameterized template |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-tls-profile-kubelet-config.yaml` | TLS profile example |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/e2e-2of2/kubeletcfg_test.go` | E2E tests showing maxPods and multi-config workflows |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/kubelet-config/kubelet_config_controller_test.go` | Unit tests with `newKubeletConfig` helper and selector patterns |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go` (lines 722–831) | Full Go type definitions for `KubeletConfig`, `KubeletConfigSpec`, `KubeletConfigStatus` |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/worker/01-worker-kubelet/_base/files/kubelet.yaml` | Default kubelet.conf showing `maxPods: 250`, `podPidsLimit: 4096` |"}],"resolvedModel":"claude-sonnet-4-6","totalDurationMs":82169,"totalTokens":43965,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1177,"cache_read_input_tokens":39936,"output_tokens":2851,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1177},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":12,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":13,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
